  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "'This.' said the old soldier suddenly, 'is the Friend of the Stars. He brought me the news yesterday. Having seen the very man Himself, in a vision, giving orders for the war.'"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "'Hm!' said his son, all deep in his broad chest. 'He came by a bazar-rumour and made profit of it.'"
  },
  {
    "tag": "p",
    "innerHtml": "His father laughed. 'At least he did not ride to me begging for a new charger, and the Gods know how many rupees. Are thy brothers' regiments also under orders?'"
  },
  {
